race.description: Ladbrokes Outdoor Enclosure Cup Day Hcp
race.comment: EARENDEL (9) has to manage an outside gate, but expect the progressive gelding to meet that challenge. Made it five wins from seven starts over 1400m here first up, and the mile holds no fears. SHY GUY (6) was beaten a whisker this track/trip seeking the hat-trick and is a threat. Has been freshened up and kept up to the mark with a Devonport trial win. Newitt's engagement indicates he's pleasing the yard. SH'BOURNE MIDNIGHT (5) is at the peak of his form, and the premier jockey stays with him. His record over this trip is good, and fitter again has winning claims as well. SHARMA'S LAST (1) has been off the scene for a year but has trialled well and has won 4/5 fresh. In the mix.
